--------------------------------
Fast Ethernet
	100BaseTX 
		Cat 5 (or better)
		100 meters from node to switch
	100BaseFX
		MM Fiber
		2 Km segments

---------------------------------
Gigabit Ethernet
	802.3ab
		1000BaseT 
			Cat 5e (or better)
			Uses all 4 pairs
			100 meters from node to switch
			[[more than you need to know!http://www.hardwaresecrets.com/article/How-Gigabit-Ethernet-Works/231/1]]
	802.3z  [[img http://img.tfd.com/cde/TWINAX.GIF]]
		1000BaseCX (rare) 
			Twinaxial cable
		1000BaseSX 
			MM fiber
			220-500 meters
		1000BaseLX
			SM fiber
			5Km
--------------------------------
10 Gig Ethernet
	Number of competing copper and fiber standards
	Copper [[img http://www.jimhayes.com/uncleted/cat6.jpg]]
		10GBaseT
			Cat 6, 60 meters
			Cat 6a, 100 meters
	Fiber [[img http://www.karishelectro.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/fiber-image.jpg]]
		10GBaseSR MM, 300 meters
		10GBaseSW MM, 300 meters
		10GBaseLR SM, 10km
		10GBaseLW SM, 10km
		10GBaseER SM, 40km
		10GBaseEW SM, 40km
	Hierarchy by distances can be remembered by
		S = short
		L = Long 
		E = Extra long (although it really stands for extended)

