Switch features
	Switches operate at the data link layer, making decisions based on MAC addresses
		That said, there are now devices called "layer-3 switches" that have some router capabilties (making decisions based on IP address) built in 
	Switch Features
		[[Auto Speed Negotiation!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autonegotiation]] (10/100/1000) (all now have)
		[[Uplink port (old) vs crossover detection (Auto MDIX)!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medium_Dependent_Interface]] 
		[[Store and forward!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Store_and_forward]] vs [[Cut Through!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cut-through_switching]]
		Managed (configurable)
		[[Rackmount!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rack_unit]]
		[[Stackable!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stackable_switch]]
		[[Power Over Ethernet!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_over_ethernet]] (PoE)
		[[switch examples!http://www.newegg.com/Store/SubCategory.aspx?SubCategory=30&Tpk=ethernet%20switch]]
	This [[wikipedia article!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_switch]] discusses most of those features
